review_blob: Had in bottle. Wish I had another. Drink alone, not with food. Coffee taste with vanilla finish.
Had in a bottle. Good beer to drink with food. Slightly stronger than blue light. Not sweet.
Served with cinnamon and sugar  on the rim of the glass. This helped to cut the bitterness of the finish. Amber in color. Nutmeg, cinnamon, and clover aroma. Festive!
Pours dark pink with a light pink head. Nice balance of sweet and tart raspberry. Good dessert beer.
Pours a cloudy pink.  Taste reminds me of a strawberry starburst. Nice finish, not bitter or hoppy.
12 ounce bottle that pours dark brown with a tan head. Hints of chocolate and coffee. Smooth and creamy with a mild finish. Enjoyable.
